<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">
<br>
"Digital Pan Tilt Zoom" allows the viewer to pan about the
      displayed image.  The controls are in the title bar.
<br><br>
With the cursor, click on any point in the image to 
recenter the image around that point.  


<br><br>
Click on the arrow buttons to move the camera's view
in the desired direction.

<br><br>
Click on the "NO ZOOM" button to zoom all the way out.

<br><br>
Click on the "ZOOM+" button to zoom in. 

<br><br>
Click on the "ZOOM-" button to zoom out.

<br><br>
Click on the "SIZE+" button to increase the size of the viewed image.

<br><br>
Click on the "SIZE-" button to decrease the size of the viewed image.

<br><br>
Click on the size "MAX" button to view the image full-sized, without
downsampling.

<br><br>
Click on the "SNAPSHOT" button to save an image.
<br><br>
Click on the "VIDEO CLIP" button to save a video clip as an AVI file.

<br><br>
Click on the "STOP" button to view a single frame instead of an 
image stream.

<br><br>
Click on the "SAVE" button to save the displayed image to your
computer.

<br><br>
If there is a "MULTI VIEW" button, click on it to bring up the 
the quad view page, which displays images from up to 9 cameras at once. 

<br><br>
If there is another button to the right of the "STOP" button
click on it to activate the relay output.  This button's text
can be set to describe what will happen when the relay output
is activated.
</font>

